                            <comment id="23489" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 29 Apr 2007 06:19:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2275&quot; title=&quot;Provide non-transactional onSetup* hook in AbstractTransactionalSpringContextTests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2275&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2275&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: After some consideration, I&apos;ve decided to simply turn &quot;onSetUp()&quot; and &quot;onTearDown()&quot; non-final. This allows for overriding these methods, implementing common setup/teardown behavior that executes in any case, either before or after the standard setup/teardown code (with those overridden methods calling the respective super method appropriately). This is also consistent with other changes that we recently did in the general test class hierarchy, relaxing the visibility and &apos;final&apos; restrictions for more flexible overriding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This change should be available in the next 2.0.5 snapshot (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/snapshots&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/snapshots&lt;/a&gt;). Please give it a try and let us know whether it works for you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
